lm provision. A major challenge of audience research is how to capture the richness of people’s social and cultural engagement with film. To achieve this, the book uses an innovative mixed-methods research and computational ontology. It develops ground-breaking theory and concepts and an innovative methodology based on an extensive data-set derived from the under-researched area of British regional film audiences.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aMotion picture audiences. 4aFilm and Media Studies 2022. 7aPERFORMING ARTS / Film & Video / History & Criticism.2bisacsh  aaudience formation.  aaudience studies.  aaudience trends.  acomputational ontology.  afilm audiences.  afilm consumption.  afilm policy.  afilm provision.  afilm, specialised and mainstream.  amixed methods.1 aForrest, David, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHanchard, Matthew, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aHanchard, Matthew, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMerrington, Peter, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aMerrington, Peter, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aTeam, the Beyond the Multiplex, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWessels, Bridgette, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertManchester University Press 2021 eBook-Packagez978311128198808iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertManchester University Press 2022 eBook-Packagez978311128144540uhttps://doi.org/10.7765/978152615784340uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781526157843423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781526157843/original  a978-3-11-128144-5  Manchester Universit